padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Has the closure of the FSS resulted in a loss of intellectual wealth through its scientists leaving the forensic science profession, or the UK? (please provide evidence/examples)</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="31" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Yes. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The closure of the FSS has caused an enormous loss of experience</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and expertise</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">from </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">the industry. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Of those that have attempted to remain in the service, the younger, or less experienced staff are more likely to be employed by FSPs as they command lower salaries</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> and </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">are aligned largely to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> short-ter</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">m</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> contracts</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. Many senior scientists, including those employed with us, have taken positions at lower comparable rates simply because the market does not support the level of salary th</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">at</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> is arguably commensurate with the</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ir</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> experience</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">  </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Others have made the move to work individually or in a collective where they </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">risk being</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> isolated from the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">mainstream competitive market</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> without access to accredited laboratory facilities </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or the economics to develop one</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="32" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Are current arrangements for the FSS’s archives satisfactory? How could arrangements for the retention of case files and forensic materials in the UK be improved?</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="33" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Our understanding is that the National Archive currently manages a large proportion of the case files, and retained materials, that were produced by the FSS. This includes a recent number of electronic case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">files that were printed out in the intervening period between the announcement of closure and closure itself, at significant cost.</span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="34" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">Some forces retain their own case files, particularly relating to those investigated most recently or </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">to</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> unsolved cases. Anyone with the appropriate authority can access the information that is held on the </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">National A</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">rchive and request a case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">file, which can be released in its entirety. </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">There is no regu</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">lation of the transference of </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">e</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">ach</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">file outside of the Archive and no audit as to the location of the case</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:normal">file once it is released. </span></li></ol><p style="background-color:#ffffff; font-size:11pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="35" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="background-color:#ffffff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:normal">In relation to retained materials, </span><span style="font-f